[3] Serbia
Date: Wed 17 Jan 2018
Source: Balkan Roundup [edited]
http://www.balkaninsight.com/en/article/murder-measles-and-new-tanks-01-17-2018


Serbia celebrated the New Year with more than 680 new cases of people infected by a curable disease, measles. Two 2-year-olds from the city of Nis, Jakov and Vuk, died just before the New Year 2018 arrived. The first death in the New Year occurred in Belgrade, where a 30-year-old man died from complications caused by the virus. The infection toll keeps rising, and the number of currently infected people stands at around 900. It is unknown when, or whether, the Ministry of Health will proclaim an epidemic, a prerequisite for adults to receive vaccinations that could prevent them from getting sick and possibly die. The total share of those infected that were unvaccinated or have unknown vaccination status stands at around 91 percent.

[Byline: Milos Ciric]

