[This analysis of the decreased number of cases of measles in California concluded stricter vaccination laws generated higher vaccination rates on average. Counties and schools in the state with poor vaccination coverage demonstrated 25-percentage-point increase in vaccinations over a period of just 2 years under the stricter regulations for exemptions. It is interesting that it took a change in policy to increase vaccination coverage where education on the importance of vaccinations failed. This suggests other states and countries should consider making vaccination with MMR mandatory for children entering school. In report [4] above on measles in France, it states that vaccination against measles is now one of the 11 mandatory vaccinations brought into force since 1 Jan this year [2018]. It will be informative to follow the impact this has on measles infection rate in school-age children in the country.

